column5: LC say what we may LC performed admirably today of course it goes without saying that management had not much to do with it LC may be the safest stock to be in under the current market conditions Value stocks always do comparatively better when volatility and corrections happen If we ever dip to the upper 2s I am buying more My biotechs also did well on the most part today again surprisingly I do not have a single traditional stock in my Fidelity portfolio All speculative stuff that will either make me a very rich man or regret ever deciding to start trading again after the debacle of 20002001 where spec B2Bs cost me dearly
